HEADWORD: Lignification
<hw>Lig`ni*fi*ca"tion</hw>
<pr>(l⟦icr⟧g`n⟦icr⟧*f⟦icr⟧*k⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>lignification</ets>. See <er>Lignify</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A change in the character of a cell wall, by
which it becomes harder. It is supposed to be due to an incrustation of
lignin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ligniform</ent>⟦br⟧
